                <note rend="inline" type="source">500. A 4e/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-22T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 11, 10 a.m.</p>
                <p>For Arnold.</p>
                <p>W. A. Burns is hereby appointed Associate Member of Tariff Revision Commission.
                    Offer of voluntary services appreciated but under statute can not be accepted.
                    Confer with Burns and telegraph amount regarded as reasonable compensation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
